cs.NI, cs.DC, cs.SI, cs.IT, cs.PF 

This paper deals with the placement and allocation of virtual network functions (VNFs) in a network, which is a topic related to network infrastructure and communication. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture). The paper also discusses the practical constraints of budget and capacity, which are related to resource allocation and optimization, making cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing) and cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) likely categories as well. The paper also involves mathematical modeling and algorithm design, which are related to information theory and optimization, making cs.IT (Information Theory) a possible category. Finally, the paper discusses the efficiency of the proposed algorithms, which is related to performance evaluation and analysis, making cs.PF (Performance) a possible category as well.
